        "content": "<p>I see that quite a few definitions about <code>SimpleGraph</code>s are <code>abbrev</code>. Is it an intentional design choice? Was it ever discussed? I had an impression that we try to give <code>def</code>s and provide API instead of relying on <code>abbrev</code>s being reducible.</p>",
        "id": 506014636,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1742170506
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>E.g., why <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SimpleGraph.Copy#doc\">docs#SimpleGraph.Copy</a> is an <code>abbrev</code> for a <code>Subtype</code> of <code>SimpleGraph.Hom</code> instead of a <code>structure</code> that <code>extends</code> it?</p>",
        "id": 506014797,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1742170652
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>SimpleGraph.Copy</code> is a very recent (one week old). I'm turning it into a <code>structure</code> in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/23090\">#23090</a></p>",
        "id": 506688797,
        "sender_full_name": "YaÃ«l Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1742380154
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Other <code>abbrev</code>s: <code>edgeSet</code>, <code>IsClique</code>, <code>IsIndepSet</code>, <code>Coloring</code>, <code>ComponentCompl</code>, <code>componentComplMk</code>, <code>coeGraph</code> (probably in some namespace), <code>hom</code> (same), <code>edgeFinset</code>, <code>LocallyFinite</code>, <code>Finsubgraph</code>, <code>FinsubgraphHom</code>, <code>completeMultipartiteGraph</code>, <code>induce</code>, <code>spanningCoe</code>, <code>Hom</code>, <code>Embedding</code>, <code>Iso</code>, <code>Hom.id</code>, <code>Hom.comp</code>, <code>Embedding.refl</code>, <code>Embedding.toHom</code>, <code>Embedding.induce</code>, <code>Embedding.spanningCoe</code>, <code>Embedding.comp</code>, <code>Iso.refl</code>, <code>Iso.toEmbedding</code>, <code>Iso.toHom</code>, <code>Iso.symm</code>, <code>Iso.comp</code>, <code>Path</code> (why not a <code>structure</code>?), <code>Subgraph.vert</code>, <code>coeSubgraph</code>, <code>restrict</code>, <code>deleteVerts</code>, <code>IsTrail.edgesFinset</code>, <code>Walk.snd</code>, <code>Walk.penultimate</code>, <code>Walk.mapLe</code>, <code>Walk.toDeleteEdges</code>, <code>Walk.toDeleteEdge</code>.</p>",
        "id": 506717078,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1742388080
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Probably, some of them should stay <code>abbrev</code>s, but I have a feeling that there is a higher density of <code>abbrev</code>s here than in the library.</p>",
        "id": 506717533,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1742388187
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note: this feeling isn't backed by numbers (where it comes to the rest of Mathlib), so I may be very wrong.</p>",
        "id": 506735771,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1742392558
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"306601\">@Kyle Miller</span> might have useful ideas here: I agree SimpleGraph.Path could be a structure (although in my opinion we should rather talk about Walk and IsPath)</p>",
